Dear Irene,

NMDS does not calculate coordinates along each axis separately (as do 
metric ordinations, e.g. cmdscale function), but it optimize the whole 
2-dimensional configuration of points. Any rotation does not change the 
configuration, but it changes coordinates along both axes. So 
coordinates along axes should not be interpreted, and correlation with 
first NMDS axis has no meaning.

Best regards,

Zoltan



